ype":"text","text":"time waited is very small, and typically it is enough so you should be controlling your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dependencies so that they do not wait for real world time to pass (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DependencyManagement"},{"type":"text","text":" for more information on how to do that)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To change the amount of time this method waits for an action, pass an explicit "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"timeout"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument, or set the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore\/timeout","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture (TCA, for short) is a library for building applications in a consistent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and understandable way, with composition, testing, and ergonomics in mind. It can be used in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI, UIKit, and more, and on any Apple platform (iOS, macOS, tvOS, and watchOS)."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture","title":"ComposableArchitecture","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/TestStore/receive(_:timeout:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-2pkzu":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Asserts